  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study evaluates antibiotic serum concentrations in correlation with perioperative fluid
      balance. Patients will be recruited in rectum and esophageal surgery (representative for low
      blood loss and restrictive fluid management) and in liver surgery (representative for high
      blood loss and liberal fluid management). The hypothesis is that high blood loss and liberal
      fluid management dilute antibiotic serum concentrations thereby potentially increasing
      surgical site infections.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
